                <h1>The Origins of North Face: A Journey into Outdoor Adventure</h1>
                <p>North Face originated in 1966 in San Francisco, founded by Douglas and Susannah Tompkins. Initially a retail store specializing in climbing gear, it evolved into a prominent outdoor apparel and equipment brand. Its name reflects the challenging, rugged northern face of a mountain, embodying their mission to equip adventurers.</p>
